title: For Sale:  Range Ammo 9mm / 45ACP / 22LR / 40 S&W
location: Racine / Franklin / Oak Creek, Racine, Wisconsin
postcontent:
Have a bunch of range ammo various brands mostly 9mm / 45ACP / 22LR with a bit of 40 S&W. Nothing fancy, just stuff I bought a couple boxes of every payday after the last time the clowns in DC caused ammo prices to go thru the roof. 

I'd be fine to just keep it on hand, but I got laid off the end of last month. My laptop decided to do a crash and burn a week ago, and this morning my wife tells me our refrigerator died... so you know where this is going LOL

I agree it's completely nuts what's happened with ammo prices and don't doubt stuff will be around 6 months from now - although higher than it was before. But in the meantime, if you need range ammo and are willing to pay a premium so you don't have to drive 100 miles to find it in stock somewhere, wave some cash in my face and we can both help each other out.

9mm /  40 S&W - $30/60 for 50/100 rounds
45 ACP - $40/80 for 50/100
22LR - $8 box of 50 or $35/50 for brick of 333/550

Brands are Winchester / Blazer Brass / Federal / S&B / Remington probably a few others I can't remember - basically what I'd buy off the shelf at Walmart or Cabela's. Let me know if there's something specific you're looking for, the pics below are just some of what I've got. I also have some JHP defense ammo in all calibers I'd consider selling if you want it bad enough to persuade me. 

While I'm doing this to get the cash, I'd be open to trade, although swapping for another gun probably defeats the purpose. But if you have silver coins or your ex-wedding ring, whatever - toss me an offer, worst I can do is say 'no'. But please don't waste your time and mine telling me I'm an evil price gouger because I won't sell for what you bought ammo for 6 months ago. If you want to camp out at Walmart at 4 am for two hours to get ammo at their retail, go for it. If your time is worth $20, make an offer and we'll both go away happy. 

Cheers!

Forgot to mention when I first put this up: as my brother-in-law the cop reminds me, it's a given I need to see a photo ID showing you're 21 since this is handgun ammo. Thanks!
